      "content": "I can't advise you to self-medicate or ignore your symptoms. The increased urinary output could be a sign of lithium toxicity, which can be serious. Drinking more water is not a substitute for medical attention, and trying to \"sleep it off\" is not a reliable way to manage symptoms. I strongly recommend scheduling an appointment with your doctor to discuss your concerns and get personalized advice.",
